prompt: 180 young pioneers from a primary school in Minhe Township went to the township nursing home to help the elderly on the "Love Day". These young pioneers were divided into 5 teams on average, and each team was divided into 4 groups of labor. How many young pioneers are there on average in each group?
summary: var1 = [find](number of young pioneers) #180, var2 = [find](number of teams) #5, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 180 / 5 = 36, var4 = [find](number of groups of labor) #4, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 36 / 4 = 9, [return](var5) # 9

prompt: In the "I Love Mom" ​​essay contest held by the school, 35 students from the fifth grade participated. The number of participants in the fourth grade is (4/7) the number of participants in the fifth grade and (5/9) the number of participants in the sixth grade. How many sixth graders are participating?
summary: var1 = [find](number of participants in fifth grade) #35, var2 = [find](ratio of participants in fourth grade to fifth grade) #(4/7), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 35 * (4/7) = 20, var4 = [find](ratio of participants in sixth grade to fifth grade) #(5/9), var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 20 / (5/9) = 36, [return](var5) # 36

prompt: When a train arrived at Anxi Station, there were 983 people, 94 people got off at Anxi Station, and 68 people got on the train. How many people were on board when leaving Anxi Station?
summary: var1 = [find](initial number of people on train) #983, var2 = [find](number of people who got off at Anxi Station) #94, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 983 - 94 = 889, var4 = [find](number of people who got on the train at Anxi Station) #68, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 889 + 68 = 957, [return](var5) # 957

prompt: Hongxing Village planted 35 trees last year, and this year planted 20 poplars and 17 willows. How many more trees are planted this year than last year?
summary: var1 = [find](number of trees planted last year) #35, var2 = [find](number of poplars planted this year) #20, var3 = [find](number of willows planted this year) #17, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 20 + 17 = 37, var5 = [subtract](var4, var1) # 37 - 35 = 2, [return](var5) # 2

prompt: There were 587 tourists in the zoo in the morning, 239 people left at noon, and 125 tourists came in the afternoon. How many visitors are there in the park at this time?
summary: var1 = [find](number of tourists in the morning) #587, var2 = [find](number of people who left at noon) #239, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 587 - 239 = 348, var4 = [find](number of tourists who came in the afternoon) #125, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 348 + 125 = 473, [return](var5) # 473

prompt: The 2010 Shanghai World Expo weekday tickets have two types: ordinary tickets and discounted tickets. The price of the discounted ticket is 90 yuan, which is 40% cheaper than the ordinary ticket. How much is the price of the ordinary ticket?
summary: var1 = [find](price of discounted ticket) #90, var2 = [find](discount percent) #40%, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 40 / 100 = 0.4, var4 = [subtract](1, var3) # 1 - 0.4 = 0.6, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 90 / 0.6 = 150, [return](var5) # 150

prompt: The school sports team has 12 male students and 13 female students. The number of chorus teams is 4 times that of the sports teams. How many people are there in the chorus team?
summary: var1 = [find](number of male students) #12, var2 = [find](number of female students) #13, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 12 + 13 = 25, var4 = [find](multiplier for chorus teams) #4, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 25 * 4 = 100, [return](var5) # 100

prompt: A farm tool factory produces a batch of furniture, plans to produce 75 sets per day, and completes it in 20 days, but actually finishes it 5 days ahead of schedule. How many units are actually produced per day?
summary: var1 = [find](number of sets planned per day) #75, var2 = [find](number of days planned for batch completion) #20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 75 * 20 = 1500, var4 = [find](actual number of days to complete batch) #15, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 1500 / 15 = 100, [return](var5) # 100

prompt: Xiaohong reads a 160-page story book. She reads (2/5) of the whole book on the first day and 25% of the whole book on the second day. How many pages did she read in total in two days?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of pages in book) #160, var2 = [multiply](var1, 2/5) # 160 * 2/5 = 64, var3 = [find](percentage of book read on second day) #25%, var4 = [multiply](var1, 25%) # 160 * 25% = 40, var5 = [add](var2, var4) # 64 + 40 = 104, [return](var5) # 104

prompt: The distance between A and B is 280 kilometers. A bus travels from A to B. After driving for 4 hours, it is still 20 kilometers away from B. How many miles per hour does the car travel on average?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between A and B) #280, var2 = [find](driving time) #4, var3 = [find](distance left to B after 4 hours) #20, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 280 - 20 = 260, var5 = [divide](var4, var2) # 260 / 4 = 65, [return](var5) # 65

prompt: When Xiao Ming reads a book, he has already read 115 pages, and the remaining pages are 20 pages a day, which takes 15 days to finish. How many pages are there in this book?
summary: var1 = [find](number of pages already read by Xiao Ming) #115, var2 = [find](based on the given information, number of days needed to complete the book) #15, var3 = [find](number of pages read per day) #20, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 15 * 20 = 300, var5 = [add](var1, var4) # 115 + 300 = 415, [return](var5) # 415

prompt: A desk is 125 yuan and an office chair is 45 yuan. How much does it cost to buy 16 sets of desks and chairs?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of a desk) #125, var2 = [find](cost of an office chair) #45, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 125 + 45 = 170, var4 = [find](number of sets of desks and chairs) #16, var5 = [multiply](var4, var3) # 16 x 170 = 2720, [return](var5) # 2720

prompt: In the orchard, 780 apple trees were planted, and 5 rows of pear trees were planted, each with 12 trees. How many times as many apple trees are there than pear trees?
summary: var1 = [find](number of apple trees) #780, var2 = [find](number of rows of pear trees) #5, var3 = [find](number of trees in each row of pear trees) #12, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 5 * 12 = 60, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 780 / 60 = 13, [return](var5) # 13

prompt: The store shipped 15 boxes of towels, each box contains 10 packs, and each pack contains 20 towels. How many towels did the store ship in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of towels) #15, var2 = [find](number of packs in each box) #10, var3 = [find](number of towels in each pack) #20, var4 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 15 * 10 = 150, var5 = [multiply](var4, var3) # 150 * 20 = 3000, [return](var5) # 3000

prompt: A certain unit of the People’s Liberation Army is marching; the team advances at a speed of 6 kilometers per hour. After 3 hours, the instructor sends a correspondent to catch up with the team at a speed of 15 kilometers per hour on a bicycle to convey the instructions of the superior. How many hours can the correspondent catch up with the team after departure?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of team) #6, var2 = [find](time traveled by team) #3, var3= [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 * 3 = 18, var4 = [find](speed of correspondent) #15, var5 = [divide](var3, [subtract](var4, var1)) # 18 / (15 - 6) = 2, [return](var5) # 2

prompt: Xiaolong and Xiaoli live in the same yard. When going to school, Xiaolong walks 80 meters per minute. It takes 7 minutes to get to school, and it takes Xiaoli 8 minutes to get to school. How many meters does Xiaoli walk per minute?
summary: var1 = [find](distance Xiaolong walks to school per minute) #80, var2 = [find](time it takes Xiaolong to get to school) #7, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 80 * 7 = 560, var4 = [find](time it takes Xiaoli to get to school) #8, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 560 / 8 = 70, [return](var5) # 70

prompt: Uncle Wang plans to produce 48 parts per day. Because of his improved technology, he completed the task of 5 days in 3 days. How many parts does he actually make every day?
summary: var1 = [find](total parts planned per day) #48, var2 = [find](total days originally planned) #5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 48 * 5 = 240, var4 = [find](actual days taken to complete task) #3, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 240 / 3 = 80, [return](var5) # 80

prompt: The cafeteria brought 4 carts of cabbage, 395 kg per cart, and 636 kg were eaten. How many kilograms of cabbage are left?
summary: var1 = [find](number of carts of cabbage) #4, var2 = [find](amount of cabbage per cart) #395, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4 * 395 = 1580, var4 = [find](amount of cabbage eaten) #636, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 1580 - 636 = 944, [return](var5) # 944

prompt: A professional household raises 420 chickens, the number of ducks is equal to that of chickens (5/6), and the number of geese is equal to that of ducks (6/7). How many geese do you raise?
summary: var1 = [find](number of chickens) #420, var2 = [multiply](var1, 5), var3 = [divide](var2, 6) # (420 * 5) / 6 = 350, var4 = [multiply](var3, 6), var5 = [divide](var4, 7) # (350 * 6) / 7 = 300, [return](var5) # 300

prompt: The supermarket ships back 8 cartons of milk, each carton has 24 bags, and the purchase price of each bag is 1.25 yuan. How much is the total purchase price of these milks?
summary: var1 = [find](number of cartons of milk shipped back) #8, var2 = [find](number of bags per carton) #24, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 * 24 = 192, var4 = [find](purchase price per bag) #1.25, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 192 * 1.25 = 240, [return](var5) # 240

prompt: Xiaojia's mother gave the salesperson 50 yuan, bought 3 fountain pens, and got back 29 yuan. How much is each fountain pen?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount given by Xiaojia's mother) #50, var2 = [find](amount of money received as change) #29, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 50 - 29 = 21, var4 = [find](number of fountain pens) #3, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 21 / 3 = 7, [return](var5) # 7

prompt: The kindergarten teacher bought a pack of candies and distributed them to the children, and each of the 35 children received 16 candies. There are 10 candies left. How many candies are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of children) #35, var2 = [find](number of candies each child got) #16, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 35 x 16 = 560, var4 = [find](number of candies left) #10, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 560 + 10 = 570, [return](var5) # 570

prompt: A professional household spent 250 yuan to buy seeds, 2.4 times more money to buy agricultural tools than to buy seeds, and 78 yuan more to buy chemical fertilizers than to buy farm tools. How much did it cost to buy chemical fertilizers?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of seeds) #250, var2 = [find](cost of agricultural tools in terms of seeds) #2.4 times of var1, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 250 * 2.4 = 600, var4 = [find](additional cost for fertilizers compared to tools) #78, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 600 + 78 = 678, [return](var5) # 678

prompt: There are 4 classes in the third grade, each class has 47 students, including 112 male students. How many female students are there?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students per class) #47, var2 = [find](number of classes) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) #47 * 4 = 188, var4 = [find](total number of male students) #112, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) #188 - 112 = 76, [return](var5) #76

prompt: There are 12 people in the art group of the school, which is 3/5 of the calligraphy group, and 5/8 of the music group. How many people are there in the music group?
summary: var1 = [find](number of people in art group) #12, var2 = [find](fraction of calligraphy group represented by art group) #3/5, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 12 * 5/3 = 20, var4 = [find](fraction of music group represented by art group) #5/8, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 20 / 5 * 8 = 32, [return](var5) # 32

prompt: Hongye Garment Factory rushed to produce 840 sets of school uniforms for Dongfeng Primary School students. It has been done for 6 days, with an average of 52 sets per day. The rest should be completed within 8 days. How many sets should be made per day on average?
summary: var1 = [find](total sets needed) #840, var2 = [find](sets completed in 6 days) #52 * 6 = 312, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) #840 - 312 = 528, var4 = [find](days left) #8, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) #528 / 8 = 66, [return](var5) #66

prompt: There are 95 story books in the library, 58 of which were lent out today, and 35 were returned. How many story books are there in the library now?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of story books in the library) #95, var2 = [find](number of story books lent out today) #58, var3 = [find](number of story books returned) #35, var4 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 95 - 58 = 37, var5 = [add](var4, var3) # 37 + 35 = 72, [return](var5) # 72

prompt: A car drives from the landowner to Luzhou, traveling 45 kilometers per hour. After driving for 2 hours, it is still 8 kilometers away from Luzhou. How many kilometers is the total distance from the landowner to Luzhou?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of the car) #45, var2 = [find](duration of travel) #2, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 45 * 2 = 90, var4 = [find](distance remaining) #8, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 90 + 8 = 98, [return](var5) # 98

prompt: The supermarket shipped back 3 trucks of apple juice, each with 8 boxes, and each box contained 12 bottles. How many bottles of apple juice were shipped back?
summary: var1 = [find](number of trucks) #3, var2 = [find](number of boxes per truck) #8, var3 = [find](number of bottles per box) #12, var4 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 3 * 8 = 24, var5 = [multiply](var4, var3) # 24 * 12 = 288, [return](var5) # 288

prompt: An average of 18.5 kilometers is repaired every day to build a section of road. After 15 days of repair, there is still 9.5 kilometers left. How long is this section of road in kilometers?
summary: var1 = [find](average distance repaired per day) #18.5, var2 = [find](number of days worked) #15, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 18.5 * 15 = 277.5, var4 = [find](distance left to be repaired) #9.5, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 277.5 + 9.5 = 287, [return](var5) # 287

prompt: A village has a total of 400 hectares of arable land, 40% of which is dry land, and 80% of the dry land is planted with cotton. How many hectares are there for planting cotton?
summary: var1 = [find](total hectares of arable land) #400, var2 = [find](percentage of dry land) #40%, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 400 * 0.4 = 160, var4 = [find](percentage of dry land planted with cotton) #80%, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 160 * 0.8 = 128, [return](var5) # 128

prompt: There are 600 kilograms of apples in the store, which have been sold for 3 days, and 120 kilograms are sold every day. How many kilograms of apples are left?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of apples) # 600, var2 = [find](number of days) # 3, var3 = [find](weight sold per day) # 120, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 3 * 120 = 360, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 600 - 360 = 240, [return](var5) # 240

prompt: To manufacture a machine, it used to require 3 tons of steel, but now it saves (1/6) compared to the original one. How many machines can be made now with the steel used to make 100 machines?
summary: var1 = [find](original amount of steel per machine) #3, var2 = [find](saving percentage) #(1/6), var3 = [multiply](var1, [subtract](1, var2)) # 3 * (1-1/6) = 2.5, var4 = [find](amount of steel used for 100 machines) #300, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 300 / 2.5 = 120, [return](var5) # 120

prompt: There are 1,500 tons of coal. After a batch of coal is transported by a train with 30 carriages of the same size, there are 150 tons left. How many tons of coal are loaded in each carriage?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of coal) #1500, var2 = [find](weight left after transporting) #150, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 1500 - 150 = 1350, var4 = [find](number of carriages) #30, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 1350 / 30 = 45, [return](var5) #45

prompt: The 29th Olympic Games will be held in Beijing, and Tianjin is also one of the co-hosting cities. From Beijing to Tianjin, a car travels 55 kilometers per hour, and after 2 hours of driving, there is still 20 kilometers away from Tianjin. How many kilometers is it from Beijing to Tianjin?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of car) #55 km/h, var2 = [find](time of driving) #2 h, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 55 * 2 = 110 km, var4 = [find](distance left from Tianjin) #20 km, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 110 + 20 = 130 km, [return](var5) # 130

prompt: A person deposited RMB 20,000 in a lump sum in the bank last month for 2 years, and the annual interest rate is 4.40%. How much interest can he get when it matures?
summary: var1 = [find](amount deposited) #20,000, var2 = [find](years deposited) #2, var3 = [find](interest rate) #4.40%, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 20,000 * 4.40% = 880, var5 = [multiply](var4, var2) # 880 * 2 = 1760, [return](var5) # 1760

prompt: "Fairy Tale World" has a total of 98 pages. Xiaoli has already read 18 pages. She will spend 5 days to read the rest. How many pages does Xiaoli read every day?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of pages in "Fairy Tale World") #98, var2 = [find](pages Xiaoli has already read) #18, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 98 - 18 = 80, var4 = [find](number of days Xiaoli will spend reading) #5, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 80 / 5 = 16, [return](var5) # 16

prompt: Yanshou Central Primary School donated 1,234 yuan for Sichuan earthquake relief, 136 yuan for the first grade, 235 yuan for the second grade, and the rest was donated by other grades. How much did the other grades donate?
summary: var1 = [find](total donation amount) #1,234, var2 = [find](donation amount for 1st grade) #136, var3 = [find](donation amount for 2nd grade) #235, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 136 + 235 = 371, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 1,234 - 371 = 863, [return](var5) # 863

prompt: The fruit shop brings in a batch of fruits and sells 14 boxes of 30 kg each, leaving 80 kg left. How many kilograms is this batch of fruit in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes sold) #14, var2 = [find](weight per box) #30, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 14 x 30 = 420, var4 = [find](leftover weight) #80, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 420 + 80 = 500, [return](var5) # 500

prompt: The school bought 640 books, which are going to be placed on 2 bookshelves. Each bookshelf has 4 layers. How many books are placed on each layer?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of books) #640, var2 = [find](number of bookshelves) #2, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 640 / 2 = 320, var4 = [find](number of layers per bookshelf) #4, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 320 / 4 = 80, [return](var5) # 80

prompt: A book has 96 pages, and Miao Miao has read (1/3) of this book and there are 15 pages less. How many pages have she read?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of pages in book) #96, var2 = [find](fraction of book Miao Miao has read) #(1/3), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 96 * (1/3) = 32, var4 = [find](number of pages less than total after reading) #15, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 32 - 15 = 17, [return](var5) # 17

prompt: Xiaohong reads a book, 25 pages a day, and finishes it in 4 days. The number of pages in the other book is three times that of this book. How many pages does the other book have?
summary: var1 = [find](pages read per day) #25, var2 = [find](days taken to finish book) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 25 * 4 = 100, var4 = [find](number of pages in first book) #100, var5 = [multiply](var4, 3) # 100 * 3 = 300, [return](var5) # 300

prompt: A story book has 80 pages. Xiao Ming reads 5 pages every day for 7 days. How many pages are left?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of pages in book) #80, var2 = [find](pages read per day) #5, var3 = [find](number of days) #7, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 5 * 7 = 35, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 80 - 35 = 45, [return](var5) # 45

prompt: The store shipped 650 kilograms of jelly and sold 16 boxes, with an average of 18 kilograms per box. How many kilograms of jelly are left?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount of jelly shipped) #650, var2 = [find](number of boxes sold) #16, var3 = [find](average amount of jelly per box) #18, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 16 * 18 = 288, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 650 - 288 = 362, [return](var5) # 362

prompt: The road construction team repaired 135 meters every day. After 25 days of repairing, there are still 210 meters left to be repaired. How long is this road?
summary: var1 = [find](number of meters repaired per day) #135, var2 = [find](number of days of repairing) #25, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 135 * 25 = 3375, var4 = [find](number of meters left to be repaired) #210, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 3375 + 210 = 3585, [return](var5) # 3585

prompt: A road repair team built a section of road with an average of 135 meters per day. It has been repaired for 44 days and there are still 520 meters left to be repaired. How long is this road in meters?
summary: var1 = [find](average meters per day of repair team) #135, var2 = [find](number of days road has been repaired) #44, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) #135 * 44 = 5940, var4 = [find](meters left to be repaired) #520, var5 = [add](var3, var4) #5940 + 520 = 6460, [return](var5) #6460

prompt: The attendance rate of Class 5(1) yesterday was 96%. There are 50 students in the whole class. How many people have to ask for leave.
summary: var1 = [find](number of students in Class 5(1)) #50, var2 = [find](attendance rate) #96%, var3 = [convert](var2) #0.96, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 50 * 0.96 = 48, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 50 - 48 = 2, [return](var5) # 2

prompt: Uncle Wang took a train from a certain city to Beijing. The train traveled 125 kilometers per hour. After 12 hours, there was still 280 kilometers to Beijing. How many kilometers is the city from Beijing?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of train) #125, var2 = [find](time traveled by train) #12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 125 * 12 = 1500, var4 = [find](distance remaining to Beijing) #280, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 1500 + 280 = 1780, [return](var5) # 1780

prompt: Two students, A and B, typed a document together. A typed 18 characters per minute, and B typed 22 characters per minute. The two students spent 30 minutes typing this document. How many characters are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](typing speed of student A) #18, var2 = [find](typing speed of student B) #22, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 18 + 22 = 40, var4 = [find](total time spent typing) #30, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 40 * 30 = 1200, [return](var5) # 1200

prompt: A book has 104 pages, Xiaojun read 19 pages, and the rest will be finished in 5 days. How many pages do you read on average every day?
summary: var1 = [find](total pages in book) #104, var2 = [find](pages Xiaojun read) #19, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 104 - 19 = 85, var4 = [find](number of days to finish rest of book) #5, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 85 / 5 = 17, [return](var5) # 17

prompt: A livestock farm in a village raises 68 chickens, 16 more ducks than chickens, and 15 times as many geese as ducks. How many geese are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of chickens) #68, var2 = [find](number of ducks relative to chickens) #16 more than var1, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 68 + 16 = 84, var4 = [find](number of geese relative to ducks) #15 times var2, var5 = [multiply](var4, var3) # 15 * 84 = 1260, [return](var5) # 1260

prompt: A tiger weighs 374.4 kg, which is 1.2 times the weight of a leopard. A bear weighs 1.5 times the weight of the leopard. How much does the bear weigh?
summary: var1 = [find](weight of tiger) #374.4, var2 = [find](multiplier for leopard to tiger) #1.2, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 374.4 / 1.2 = 312, var4 = [find](multiplier for bear to leopard) #1.5, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 312 * 1.5 = 468, [return](var5) # 468

prompt: Master Li processed a batch of parts. He originally planned to process 50 parts per day and completed them in 30 days. He actually processed 60 parts per day. How many days did he complete the task?
summary: var1 = [find](planned parts per day) #50, var2 = [find](number of days taken to complete planned parts) #30, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 50 * 30 = 1500, var4 = [find](actual parts per day) #60, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 1500 / 60 = 25, [return](var5) # 25

prompt: Jiawei Beverage Factory has produced 6,000 bottles of yoghurt. Every 12 bottles are packed in a box, and every 10 boxes are packed in a box. How many boxes of these yogurt can be packed?
summary: var1 = [find](number of bottles of yogurt produced) #6000, var2 = [find](number of bottles in each box) #12, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 6000 / 12 = 500, var4 = [find](number of boxes in each large box) #10, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 500 / 10 = 50, [return](var5) # 50

prompt: A road construction team builds a road of 1800m in 15 days, and actually builds 20m more than planned every day. How much is the original plan to build roads per day?
summary: var1 = [find](length of road built) #1800m, var2 = [find](number of days taken to build) #15, var3 = [subtract](var1, 20*var2) # 1800 - (20*15) = 1500, var4 = [divide](var1, var2) # 1800 / 15 = 120, var5 = [subtract](var4, 20) # 120 - 20 = 100, [return](var5) # 100

prompt: The orchard harvested 300 boxes of apples and 260 boxes of pears. How many times does it take for a truck to transport 40 boxes at a time?

prompt: There are 5 classes in the fourth grade, with 58 students in each class, including 130 girls. How many boys are there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of classes) # 5, var2 = [find](number of students in each class) # 58, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 5 x 58 = 290, var4 = [find](number of girls) # 130, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 290 - 130 = 160, [return](var5) # 160

prompt: Xiao Ming wants to buy some stationery with 100 yuan. He first bought 9 notebooks for 45 yuan, and plans to use the rest of the money to buy pens, each pen is 2.5 yuan. How many pens can Xiao Ming buy?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount of money) # 100, var2 = [find](cost of notebooks) # 45, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 100 - 45 = 55, var4 = [find](cost of 1 pen) # 2.5, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 55 / 2.5 = 22, [return](var5) # 22

prompt: The binding team used paper to bind exercise books. One exercise book had 40 sheets. After 75 books were bound, there were 32 sheets left. How many sheets were there?
summary: var1 = [find](number of sheets in one exercise book) #40, var2 = [find](number of exercise books bound) #75, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 40 * 75 = 3000, var4 = [find](number of sheets left) #32, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 3000 + 32 = 3032, [return](var5) # 3032

prompt: There are 180 volleyballs in the sporting goods store, and 10 fewer basketballs than 4 times the number of volleyballs. How many basketballs and volleyballs are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of volleyballs) #180, var2 = [find](4 times the number of volleyballs) #720, var3 = [subtract](var2, 10) # 720 - 10 = 710, var4 = [find](number of basketballs) = var3, var5 = [add](var1, var4) # 180 + 710 = 890, [return](var5) # 890

prompt: Zhang Lin wants to practice playing table tennis. A table tennis racket costs 7.8 yuan and a table tennis ball costs 1.5 yuan. Zhang Lin bought a racket and a table tennis ball with 10 yuan. How much should he get back?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of table tennis racket) #7.8, var2 = [find](cost of table tennis ball) #1.5, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 7.8 + 1.5 = 9.3, var4 = [find](amount of money spent) #10, var5 = [subtract](var4, var3) # 10 - 9.3 = 0.7, [return](var5) # 0.7

prompt: There are 286 boys and 265 girls in the fourth grade. Among them, 176 students signed up for the long-distance running. How many students did not sign up?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boys in fourth grade) #286, var2 = [find](number of girls in fourth grade) #265, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 286 + 265 = 551, var4 = [find](number of students who signed up) #176, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 551 - 176 = 375, [return](var5) # 375

prompt: The students hit the ball. Xiaojun took 108 shots, Xiaohong took 47 more shots than Xiaojun, and Xiaofang took 13 shots less than Xiaohong. How many shots did Xiao Fang take?
summary: var1 = [find](number of shots taken by Xiaojun) #108, var2 = [find](number of extra shots taken by Xiaohong compared to Xiaojun) #47, var3 = [add](var2, var1) # 47 + 108 = 155, var4 = [find](number of shots taken by Xiaofang compared to Xiaohong) #13, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 155 - 13 = 142, [return](var5) # 142

prompt: A table costs 64 yuan, and a chair costs 36 yuan. The company bought 30 sets of tables and chairs. How much does it cost in total?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of a table) #64, var2 = [find](cost of a chair) #36, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 64 + 36 = 100, var4 = [find](number of sets of tables and chairs) #30, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 100 * 30 = 3000, [return](var5) # 3000

prompt: There are 9 liters of alcohol, which need to be filled in bottles of the same size. It is known that 6 bottles can hold 1.5 liters. How many such bottles are needed to fill all the alcohol?
summary: var1 = [find](total liters of alcohol) #9, var2 = [find](liters that one bottle can hold) #1.5, var3 = [find](number of bottles that can hold 1.5 liters) #6, var4 = [divide](var2, var3) # 1.5 / 6 = 0.25, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 9 / 0.25 = 36, [return](var5) # 36

prompt: The school built a new teaching building with 4 floors, 5 classrooms on each floor, and 12 fluorescent lamps installed in each classroom. How many fluorescent lamps are installed in this teaching building?
summary: var1 = [find](number of floors) #4, var2 = [find](number of classrooms per floor) #5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4 * 5 = 20, var4 = [find](number of fluorescent lamps per classroom) #12, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 20 * 12 = 240, [return](var5) # 240

prompt: The students watered 23 trees in the third grade, twice as many in the fourth grade, and 18 more trees in the sixth grade than in the third and fourth grades. How many trees did the sixth grade water in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of trees watered in third grade) #23, var2 = [multiply](var1, 2) # 23 * 2 = 46, var3 = [find](number of trees watered in fourth grade) #46, var4 = [add](var1, var3) # 23 + 46 = 69, var5 = [add](var4, 18) # 69 + 18 = 87, [return](var5) # 87

prompt: There are 840 students in Guangming Primary School. The fifth grade accounts for 2/7 of the school's students, and the fifth grade girls account for this grade (5/12). How many girls are there in the fifth grade?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students) #840, var2 = [find](fraction of students in fifth grade) #2/7, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 840 * 2/7 = 240, var4 = [find](fraction of girls in fifth grade) #5/12, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 240 * 5/12 = 100, [return](var5) # 100

prompt: The supermarket shipped 8 boxes of eggs, each weighing 12 kilograms, and after selling some, there were 42 kilograms left. How many kilograms were sold?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of eggs) #8, var2 = [find](weight per box) #12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 x 12 = 96, var4 = [find](remaining weight) #42, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 96 - 42 = 54, [return](var5) # 54

prompt: A passenger train and a freight train depart from A and B at the same time, travel towards each other, and meet each other after 6 hours. Passenger cars travel an average of 112 kilometers per hour, and trucks travel an average of 88 kilometers per hour. How many kilometers are there between A and B?
summary: var1 = [find](time taken for trains to meet) #6, var2 = [find](average speed of passenger train) #112, var3 = [find](average speed of freight train) #88, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 112 + 88 = 200, var5 = [multiply](var4, var1) # 200 * 6 = 1200, [return](var5) # 1200

prompt: Lingling's height is 1.42 meters. Standing on a stool with a height of 0.4 meters, she is 0.15 meters taller than her mother. How many meters is her mother's height?
summary: var1 = [find](Lingling's height) #1.42, var2 = [find](height of stool) #0.4, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 1.42 + 0.4 = 1.82, var4 = [find](height difference between Lingling and her mother) #0.15, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 1.82 - 0.15 = 1.67, [return](var5) # 1.67

prompt: There is a kind of iron wire that is 8 meters long and weighs 2 kilograms. There are 300 meters of this kind of iron wire. How many kilograms does it weigh in total?
summary: var1 = [find](length of iron wire) #8, var2 = [find](weight of iron wire) #2, var3 = [divide](var2, var1) # 2 / 8 = 0.25, var4 = [find](total length of iron wire) #300, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 0.25 * 300 = 75, [return](var5) # 75

prompt: The students went out to plant trees. There are 56 girls and 28 boys. Every 6 people are divided into groups. How many groups can they be divided into?
summary: var1 = [find](number of girls) #56, var2 = [find](number of boys) #28, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 56 + 28 = 84, var4 = [find](number of people in each group) #6, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 84 / 6 = 14, [return](var5) # 14

prompt: Two cars A and B are traveling toward each other from two places 340 kilometers apart at the same time. Car A travels 80 kilometers per hour, and car B travels 90 kilometers per hour. How many hours later will the two cars meet?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between two cars) #340, var2 = [find](speed of car A) #80, var3 = [find](speed of car B) #90, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 80 + 90 = 170, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 340 / 170 = 2, [return](var5) # 2

prompt: 8400 kg of pears are transported from the orchard, which is 100 kg less than 4 times the number of kilograms of apples transported. How many kilograms of apples are transported?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of pears) #8400, var2 = [find](weight difference between pears and apples) #100, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 8400 + 100 = 8500, var4 = [find](multiplier for apples) #4, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 8500 / 4 = 2125, [return](var5) # 2125

prompt: The farm tool factory plans to produce 400 farm tools in 25 days, but it is actually completed 5 days ahead of schedule. How many farm tools are actually produced on average per day?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of farm tools produced)#400, var2 = [find](number of days planned to produce the tools)#25, var3 = [find](days completed ahead of schedule)#5, var4 = [subtract](var2, var3) #25 - 5 = 20, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 400 / 20 = 20, [return](var5) # 20

prompt: Huanhuan is 10 years old this year, and his father is 2 years older than Huanhuan, three times as old. How old is his father this year?
summary: var1 = [find](age of Huanhuan) #10, var2 = [find](age multiplier for father) #3, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 10 * 3 = 30, var4 = [find](age difference between Huanhuan and his father) #2, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 30 + 2 = 32, [return](var5) # 32

prompt: A car travels an average of 70 kilometers per hour in the first 5 hours, and an average of 35 kilometers per hour in the next 2 hours. How many kilometers per hour does the car travel on average?
summary: var1 = [find](distance traveled in first 5 hours) #70 * 5 = 350, var2 = [find](distance traveled in next 2 hours) #35 * 2 = 70, var3 = [find](total time traveled) #5 + 2 = 7, var4 = [find](total distance traveled) #350 + 70 = 420, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 420 / 7 = 60, [return](var5) # 60

prompt: Beibei’s money to buy a 5.9-yuan notebook is 0.6 yuan short, and he buys a 4.8-yuan notebook, and the remaining money just buys a ballpoint pen. How much is this ballpoint pen?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of first notebook) #5.9, var2 = [find](shortage of money) #0.6, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 5.9 - 0.6 = 5.3, var4 = [find](cost of second notebook) #4.8, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 5.3 - 4.8 = 0.5, [return](var5) # 0.5

prompt: The distance between A and B is 480 kilometers. The express train departs from A and the slow train departs from B at the same time. It is known that the express train travels 70 kilometers per hour and the slow train travels 50 kilometers per hour. The two vehicles meet at C on the way. How many miles is the distance between C and A?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between A and B) #480, var2 = [find](speed of express train) #70, var3 = [find](speed of slow train) #50, var4 = [find](time to meet at C) # var1 / (var2 + var3) # 480 / (70 + 50) = 4, var5 = [find](distance from A to C) # var2 * var4 # 70 * 4 = 280, [return](var5) # 280

prompt: On the weekend, 5 members of Xiaoyang's family went mountaineering. They brought 2 travel bags, and 5 of them took turns carrying them. They walked 15 kilometers. How many kilometers did each person travel with their backpacks on average?
summary: var1 = [find](number of family members) #5, var2 = [find](number of travel bags) #2, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 5 / 2 = 2.5, var4 = [find](total distance walked) #15, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 15 / 2.5 = 6, [return](var5) # 6

prompt: The schoolbags are 82 yuan each, and the pencil cases are 18 yuan each. Now I want to buy one set for each of the 32 students in the class. How much will it cost in total?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of a schoolbag) #82, var2 = [find](cost of a pencil case) #18, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 82 + 18 = 100, var4 = [find](number of students) #32, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 100 * 32 = 3200, [return](var5) # 3200

prompt: The school bought 8 bookshelves, each with 5 layers, and each layer can hold 35 books. How many books can these bookshelves hold in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of bookshelves) #8, var2 = [find](number of layers per bookshelf) #5, var3 = [find](number of books per layer) #35, var4 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 * 5 = 40, var5 = [multiply](var4, var3) # 40 * 35 = 1400, [return](var5) # 1400

prompt: A box of 12 pens, each 5 yuan, 36 boxes of pens in a box. How much is a box of pens?
summary: var1 = [find](number of pens in a box) #12, var2 = [find](cost of each pen) #5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 12 x 5 = 60, var4 = [find](number of boxes in one big box) #36, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 60 x 36 = 2160, [return](var5) # 2160

prompt: The cement factory produces a batch of cement. The original plan is to produce 126.5 tons of cement per day, which will be completed in 30 days. It actually took only 25 days to complete the task. How many tons of cement is actually produced on average every day?
summary: var1 = [find](original plan in tons per day) #126.5, var2 = [find](number of days planned) #30, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 126.5 * 30 = 3795, var4 = [find](actual days taken) #25, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 3795 / 25 = 151.8, [return](var5) # 151.8

prompt: Team A and Team B jointly build a road. Team A builds an average of 235 meters per day, and Team B builds an average of 48 meters less than Team A per day. They completed the task in 8 days. How many meters is this road?
summary: var1 = [find](average daily progress of Team A in meters) #235, var2 = [find](average daily progress of Team B in meters) #var1 - 48, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 235 + (235-48) = 422, var4 = [find](number of days) #8, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 422 x 8 = 3376, [return](var5) # 3376

prompt: There are 12 boxes of yogurt and 15 boxes of fruit juice, and each box contains 24 bottles. How many bottles of beverages are there in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of yogurt) #12, var2 = [find](number of boxes of fruit juice) #15, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 12 + 15 = 27, var4 = [find](number of bottles in each box) #24, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 27 * 24 = 648, [return](var5) # 648

prompt: A building has 6 floors, and each floor has 8 units. The total area of ​​this building is 7020 square meters. How many square meters does each house have on average?
summary: var1 = [find](number of floors) #6, var2 = [find](units per floor) #8, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 * 8 = 48, var4 = [find](total area of building) #7020, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 7020 / 48 = 146.25, [return](var5) # 146.25

prompt: There are 640 popular science books in the Tiantian Bookstore of the school, which is 60% more than the number of story books. How many story books does Tiantian Bookstore have?
summary: var1 = [find](total science books) #640, var2 = [find](percent increase) #60, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 60 / 100 = 0.6, var4 = [add](var3, 1) # 0.6 + 1 = 1.6, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 640 / 1.6 = 400, [return](var5) # 400

prompt: There are 36 baskets of apples in a store, and each basket weighs 40 kilograms. The weight of apples shipped is 8 times that of pears. How many kilograms of pears are shipped?
summary: var1 = [find](number of baskets of apples) #36, var2 = [find](weight of each basket of apples) #40, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 36 * 40 = 1440, var4 = [find](weight of apples shipped) #8, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 1440 / 8 = 180, [return](var5) # 180

prompt: Two engineering teams, A and B, jointly repair a road with a length of 5500 meters. Team A repairs 120 meters per day, and team B repairs 100 meters per day. How many days will it take for the two teams to build this road together?
summary: var1 = [find](length of road) #5500, var2 = [find](team A's daily repair rate) #120, var3 = [find](team B's daily repair rate) #100, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 120 + 100 = 220, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 5500 / 220 = 25, [return](var5) # 25

prompt: The transportation team has to transport 1,000 bags of chemical fertilizers, but 271 bags have been transported, and the remaining 81 bags will be transported each time. How many times will they be transported?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of bags to be transported) #1000, var2 = [find](number of bags already transported) #271, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 1000 - 271 = 729, var4 = [find](number of bags to be transported each time) #81, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 729 / 81 = 9, [return](var5) # 9

prompt: Xiao Xing reads a story book. He reads (1/5) of the whole book on the first day and (1/6) of the whole book on the second day. He reads 33 pages in total in two days. How many pages does this book have?
summary: var1 = [find](fraction of book read on first day) #1/5, var2 = [find](fraction of book read on second day) #1/6, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 1/5 + 1/6 = 11/30, var4 = [find](total number of pages read in 2 days) #33, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 33 / (11/30) = 90, [return](var5) # 90

prompt: A cargo ship carries 3200 tons of goods, unloads 1850 tons at the port, and loads 1000 tons of other goods. How many tons of cargo are on board now?
summary: var1 = [find](initial amount of goods on ship) #3200, var2 = [find](amount of goods unloaded at port) #1850, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 3200 - 1850 = 1350, var4 = [find](amount of goods loaded onto ship) #1000, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 1350 + 1000 = 2350, [return](var5) # 2350

prompt: A library bought 6 bookshelves, each shelf has 5 layers, and each layer can hold 35 books. How many books can these bookshelves hold in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of bookshelves) #6, var2 = [find](number of layers in each shelf) #5, var3 = [find](number of books each layer can hold) #35, var4 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 * 5 = 30, var5 = [multiply](var4, var3) # 30 * 35 = 1050, [return](var5) # 1050

prompt: The school plans to distribute exercise books to 16 classes, each class has 240 copies, and 800 copies are needed for spare. How many exercise books should schools buy?
summary: var1 = [find](number of classes) #16, var2 = [find](number of copies per class) #240, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 16 * 240 = 3840, var4 = [find](number of spare copies needed) #800, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 3840 + 800 = 4640, [return](var5) # 4640

prompt: 40 workers can complete a batch of parts in 30 hours. If some workers ask for leave temporarily, the rest of the workers will have to spend 50 hours to complete the batch of parts. How many people ask for leave?
summary: var1 = [find](number of workers) #40, var2 = [find](total time for completion of batch) #30, var3 = [find](revised time for completion of batch) #50, var4 = [divide]([multiply](var1, var2), var3) # (40 x 30) / 50 = 24, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 40 - 24 = 16, [return](var5) # 16

prompt: The school makes 2 curtains for each class. The price of each curtain is 48 yuan. There are 20 classes in the school. How much is the total cost?
summary: var1 = [find](number of curtains per class) #2, var2 = [find](price per curtain) #48, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 2 x 48 = 96, var4 = [find](number of classes) #20, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 96 x 20 = 1920, [return](var5) # 1920

prompt: There are 184 tons of goods in one pile. After transporting part of the goods with 4 cars, there are still 20 tons of goods left. How many tons of goods are transported by each car on average?
summary: var1 = [find](total tons of goods) #184, var2 = [find](remaining tons of goods) #20, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 184 - 20 = 164, var4 = [find](number of cars) #4, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 164 / 4 = 41, [return](var5) # 41

prompt: The original price of a tape recorder is 220 yuan, and the price will be reduced by 20% for the "11th". How much is the current price? ．
summary: var1 = [find](original price of tape recorder) #220, var2 = [find](discount percentage) #20, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 20 / 100 = 0.2, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 220 * 0.2 = 44, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 220 - 44 = 176, [return](var5) # 176

prompt: The students participated in the art gymnastics performance. 336 students were arranged in 7 square formations, and each square formation stood in 4 rows. How many students were there in each row?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students) #336, var2 = [find](number of square formations) #7, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 336 / 7 = 48, var4 = [find](number of rows in each formation) #4, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 48 / 4 = 12, [return](var5) # 12

prompt: There are 405 seats downstairs in the children's theater and 9 rows upstairs with 32 seats in each row. How many seats are there in total in the children's theater?
summary: var1 = [find](number of seats downstairs) #405, var2 = [find](number of rows upstairs) #9, var3 = [find](number of seats per row) #32, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 9 * 32 = 288, var5 = [add](var1, var4) # 405 + 288 = 693, [return](var5) # 693

prompt: There are 84 cars parked in the parking lot. In the morning, 30 cars drove away, and 8 cars came in. How many cars are there in the parking lot at this time?
summary: var1 = [find](number of cars initially parked) #84, var2 = [find](number of cars drove away) #30, var3 = [find](number of cars came in) #8, var4 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 84 - 30 = 54, var5 = [add](var4, var3) # 54 + 8 = 62, [return](var5) # 62

prompt: Wang Ping plans to read a novel. He reads an average of 28 pages per day in the first 4 days, and 21 pages per day in the next 3 days. How many pages does Wang Ping read on average per day?
summary: var1 = [find](number of pages read in the first 4 days) #28*4 = 112, var2 = [find](number of pages read in the next 3 days) #21*3 = 63, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 112 + 63 = 175, var4 = [find](number of days) #4+3 = 7, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 175 / 7 = 25, [return](var5) # 25

prompt: The store brings in 16 boxes of men's shirts and 18 boxes of women's shirts, with 25 pieces in each box. How many pieces of shirts are shipped in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of men's shirts) #16, var2 = [find](number of boxes of women's shirts) #18, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 16 + 18 = 34, var4 = [find](number of pieces in each box) #25, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 34 x 25 = 850, [return](var5) # 850

prompt: The library buys back a batch of new books, 60 books are placed on each floor, and each bookshelf has 4 floors, and a total of 15 such bookshelves are filled. How many new books did the library buy back?
summary: var1 = [find](number of books per floor) #60, var2 = [find](number of floors per bookshelf) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 60 * 4 = 240, var4 = [find](number of bookshelves) #15, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 240 * 15 = 3600, [return](var5) # 3600

prompt: There were 1262 tourists in the Science and Technology Park on Monday. There were 738 tourists in the morning and 525 in the afternoon on Tuesday. How many tourists are there in these two days?
summary: var1 = [find](number of tourists on Monday) #1262, var2 = [find](number of tourists on Tuesday morning) #738, var3 = [find](number of tourists on Tuesday afternoon) #525, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 738 + 525 = 1263, var5 = [add](var1, var4) # 1262 + 1263 = 2525, [return](var5) # 2525

prompt: The cafeteria bought 3 baskets of cucumbers, each weighing 25 kilograms; and 36 kilograms of beans. How many kilograms more cucumbers are bought than beans?
summary: var1 = [find](number of baskets of cucumbers) #3, var2 = [find](weight of each basket of cucumbers) #25, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 3 x 25 = 75, var4 = [find](weight of beans) #36, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 75 - 36 = 39, [return](var5) # 39

prompt: Mom takes Xiao Ming to see grandma by long-distance bus. It departs at 8 am and arrives at 12 noon. The speed of the car is 80 kilometers per hour. How many kilometers is it from Xiao Ming's house to grandma's house?
summary: var1 = [find](departure time) #8 am, var2 = [find](arrival time) #12 noon, var3 = [subtract](var2, var1) # 12 - 8 = 4 hours, var4 = [find](speed of the bus) #80 kilometers per hour, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 4 * 80 = 320 kilometers, [return](var5) # 320

prompt: A car travels 160 kilometers per hour from point A to point B. It has been driving for 12 hours, and it is still 485 kilometers away from point B. How many kilometers is it from point A to point B?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of the car) #160, var2 = [find](time traveled by the car) #12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 160 * 12 = 1920, var4 = [find](distance left to travel) #485, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 1920 + 485 = 2405, [return](var5) # 2405

prompt: Uncle Liu drove from city A to city B. The average driving speed is 65.5 kilometers per hour. After 1.6 hours, there is still 36.5 kilometers away from city B. Find the distance between cities A and B?
summary: var1 = [find](average driving speed) # 65.5, var2 = [find](time taken) # 1.6, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 65.5 * 1.6 = 104.8, var4 = [find](distance left) # 36.5, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 104.8 + 36.5 = 141.3, [return](var5) # 141.3

prompt: Lin Li weighed 3.25 kg when she was born, and 7 kg after 3 months. How many kilograms does Lin Li's weight increase per month on average?
summary: var1 = [find](Lin Li's weight at birth) #3.25, var2 = [find](Lin Li's weight after 3 months) #7, var3 = [subtract](var2, var1) # 7 - 3.25 = 3.75, var4 = [find](number of months passed) #3, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 3.75 / 3 = 1.25, [return](var5) # 1.25

prompt: Xiaoxiao bought 3 boxes of ballpoint pens, 12 in each box, and 2 yuan each. How much does it cost in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of ballpoint pens) #3, var2 = [find](number of ballpoint pens in each box) #12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 3 * 12 = 36, var4 = [find](cost of each ballpoint pen) #2, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 36 * 2 = 72, [return](var5) # 72

prompt: Aunt Li bought 3,000 yuan of national bonds, fixed for 3 years, with an annual interest rate of 3.14%. How much interest will she get when it matures?
summary: var1 = [find](amount Aunt Li bought in yuan) #3000, var2 = [find](fixed term in years) #3, var3 = [find](annual interest rate as decimal) #0.0314, var4 = [multiply](var1, var3) # 3000 * 0.0314 = 94.2, var5 = [multiply](var4, var2) # 94.2 * 3 = 282.6, [return](var5) # 282.6

prompt: A large chicken farm packs 25 kilograms of eggs into a box for one day. After packing 37 boxes, there are 19 kilograms left. How many kilograms of eggs are collected on this day?
summary: var1 = [find](amount of eggs per box) #25, var2 = [find](number of boxes packed) #37, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 25 * 37 = 925, var4 = [find](remaining kilograms of eggs) #19, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 925 + 19 = 944, [return](var5) # 944

prompt: The canteen of Xiuli Middle School used 6.16 tons of coal this month, which was 12% less than last month. How many tons of coal was used last month?
summary: var1 = [find](coal used this month) #6.16, var2 = [find](percentage decrease) #12%, var3 = [divide](var2, 100) # 12 / 100 = 0.12, var4 = [subtract](1, var3) # 1 - 0.12 = 0.88, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 6.16 / 0.88 = 7, [return](var5) # 7

prompt: There are 45 students in class one of the third grade, and each of them has participated in at least one of the two sports activities of rope skipping and long-distance running. There are 28 people participating in the rope skipping activity and 30 people participating in the long-distance running activity. How many people participated in both activities?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of students in class) #45, var2 = [find](number of students participating in rope skipping activity) #28, var3 = [find](number of students participating in long-distance running activity) #30, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 28 + 30 = 58, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 45 - 58 = -13, [return](abs(var5)) # 13

prompt: There were 18 passengers on the bus, 5 people got off at the district government station, and 7 people got on the bus. How many passengers are there on the bus?
summary: var1 = [find](number of passengers on bus) #18, var2 = [find](number of people who got off) #5, var3 = [find](number of people who got on) #7, var4 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 18 - 5 = 13, var5 = [add](var4, var3) # 13 + 7 = 20, [return](var5) # 20

prompt: The two masters and apprentices rushed to make a batch of parts. The master made 15 per hour, and the apprentice made 12 per hour. The two worked together for 5 hours to complete the work. How many parts are there in this batch?
summary: var1 = [find](rate of master) #15, var2 = [find](rate of apprentice) #12, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 15 + 12 = 27, var4 = [find](time taken) #5, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 27 x 5 = 135, [return](var5) # 135

prompt: A pile of yellow sand weighs 150 tons, and it has been transported 13 times by a truck with a load of 8 tons. How many tons are left?
summary: var1 = [find](weight of yellow sand pile) #150 tons, var2 = [find](number of times transported) #13, var3 = [find](load capacity of truck) #8 tons, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 13 * 8 = 104, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 150 - 104 = 46, [return](var5) # 46

prompt: The distance between A and B is 630 kilometers. Cars A and B drive from the two places at the same time and meet each other after 4.5 hours. It is known that car A travels 80 kilometers per hour. How many kilometers does car B travel per hour?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between A and B) #630 km, var2 = [find](time it takes for cars to meet) #4.5 hrs, var3 = [find](speed of car A) #80 km/hour, var4 = [divide](var1, var2) # 630 / 4.5 = 140 km/hour, var5 = [subtract](var4, var3) # 140 - 80 = 60 km/hour, [return](var5) # 60

prompt: Aunt Wang used 50 yuan to buy 16.5 kilograms of rice, and she had to pay 2.40 yuan per kilogram of rice. How much should the salesperson give Aunt Wang?
summary: var1 = [find](money used by Aunt Wang) #50, var2 = [find](weight of rice bought) #16.5, var3 = [find](cost per kilogram of rice) #2.40, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 16.5 * 2.40 = 39.6, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 50 - 39.6 = 10.4, [return](var5) # 10.4

prompt: Class 3 (1) donated 960 books to the disaster-stricken students, 6 books were bundled into a bundle, and 8 bundles were packed into a box. How many boxes can it hold?
summary: var1 = [find](number of books donated) # 960, var2 = [find](number of books per bundle) # 6, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 960 / 6 = 160, var4 = [find](number of bundles per box) # 8, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 160 / 8 = 20, [return](var5) # 20

prompt: There are 6 cowsheds in the dairy farm, and there are 8 cows in each cowshed. A total of 960 kilograms of feed is fed a day. How many kilograms of feed is fed to each cow on average?
summary: var1 = [find](number of cowsheds) #6, var2 = [find](number of cows in each cowshed) #8, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 x 8 = 48, var4 = [find](total kilograms of feed fed per day) #960, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 960 / 48 = 20, [return](var5) # 20

prompt: The department store sells 5 boxes of tops, 20 pieces in each box, and 42 yuan each. How much is it sold in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of tops) #5, var2 = [find](number of pieces in each box) #20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 5 * 20 = 100, var4 = [find](price per box) #42, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 100 * 42 = 4200, [return](var5) # 4200

prompt: Xinxing Machine Tool Factory will produce 720 machine tools. It is planned to produce 80 units per day, but the actual production is 10 units more than planned per day. How many days can the task be completed?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of machine tools to produce) #720, var2 = [find](units to produce per day) #80, var3 = [find](units produced more than planned per day) #10, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 80 + 10 = 90, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 720 / 90 = 8, [return](var5) # 8

prompt: Aunt Wang went to buy 3 footballs, paid 100 to the salesperson, and got 7 yuan back. How much is an average football?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount paid) #100, var2 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 100 - 7 = 93, var3 = [find](change received) #7, var4 = [find](number of footballs) #3, var5 = [divide](var2, var4) # 93 / 3 = 31, [return](var5) #31

prompt: Uncle Zhang used (2/3) of the 20 hectares of land to grow roses, of which red roses accounted for (3/5) of the rose planting area. How many hectares of red roses did Uncle Zhang win?
summary: var1 = [find](total hectares of land) #20, var2 = [find](percentage used for roses) #(2/3), var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 20 * (2/3) = 13.33 (rounded to 13), var4 = [find](percentage of red roses) #(3/5), var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 13 * (3/5) = 7.8 (rounded to 8), [return](var5) # 8

prompt: Dad spent 0.8 yuan to buy 500 grams of tomatoes, and 2.6 yuan to buy a cabbage. How much did it cost in total?
summary: var1 = [find](cost of tomatoes per gram) #0.8/500, var2 = [find](weight of tomatoes) # 500, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 0.8/500 * 500 = 0.8, var4 = [find](cost of cabbage) # 2.6, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 0.8 + 2.6 = 3.4, [return](var5) # 3.4

prompt: 56 children lined up to go on a spring outing. From the top of the line, Xiao Gang was the 19th, and from the bottom of the line, Xiao Li was the 12th. How many classmates are there between Xiaogang and Xiaoli?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of children) #56, var2 = [find](Xiao Gang's position from top) #19, var3 = [find](Xiao Li's position from bottom) #12, var4 = [subtract](var1, var3) # 56 - 12 = 44, var5 = [subtract](var4, var2) # 44 - 19 = 25, [return](var5) # 25

prompt: Teacher Li bought 2 pairs of badminton rackets, paid 70 yuan, and got 6 yuan back. How much is each badminton racket?
summary: var1 = [find](number of pairs of badminton rackets) #2, var2 = [find](total cost) #70, var3 = [find](change received) #6, var4 = [subtract](var2, var3) # 70 - 6 = 64, var5 = [divide](var4, var1) # 64 / 2 = 32, [return](var5) # 32

prompt: The school organizes students to visit Quyuan Temple. There are 670 people who visit in the morning and 3 batches in the afternoon, 136 people in each batch. How many students are there to visit on this day?
summary: var1 = [find](number of students who visit in the morning) #670, var2 = [find](number of batches in the afternoon) #3, var3 = [find](number of students in each batch) #136, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 3 * 136 = 408, var5 = [add](var1, var4) # 670 + 408 = 1078, [return](var5) #1078

prompt: A and B process parts. A processes 65 pieces per hour, B processes 75 pieces per hour, and the two work for 12 hours. How many parts are processed in total?
summary: var1 = [find](rate of processing for A) #65, var2 = [find](rate of processing for B) #75, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 65 + 75 = 140, var4 = [find](total hours worked) #12, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 140 * 12 = 1680, [return](var5) # 1680

prompt: There are 24 boys and 19 girls in the third grade of Hope Primary School. The number of people in the whole school is 6 times that of the third grade. How many people are there in Hope Primary School?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boys in third grade) #24, var2 = [find](number of girls in third grade) #19, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 24 + 19 = 43, var4 = [find](multiplier for whole school) #6, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 43 * 6 = 258, [return](var5) # 258

prompt: A bee flies 24.6 kilometers at 1.5 hours, which is 2.5 times the speed of a butterfly. How many kilometers does the butterfly fly per hour?
summary: var1 = [find](distance flown by bee) #24.6, var2 = [find](time taken by bee in hours) #1.5, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 24.6 / 1.5 = 16.4, var4 = [find](speed of bee), var5 = [divide](var4, 2.5) # 16.4 / 2.5 = 6.56, [return](var5) # 6.56

prompt: Master Wang makes 70 parts per hour, and Master Li makes 50 parts per hour. The two start working at the same time and cooperate to make 840 parts. How many hours will it take to complete?
summary: var1 = [find](rate of production for Master Wang) #70, var2 = [find](rate of production for Master Li) #50, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 70 + 50 = 120, var4 = [find](total number of parts to make) #840, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 840 / 120 = 7, [return](var5) # 7

prompt: The canteen bought 6 boxes of condiments and spent a total of 432 yuan. There are 24 bottles of condiments in each box. How much is each bottle of condiments?
summary: var1 = [find](number of boxes of condiments) #6, var2 = [find](total cost of boxes) #432, var3 = [divide](var2, var1) # 432 / 6 = 72, var4 = [find](number of bottles per box) #24, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 72 / 24 = 3, [return](var5) # 3

prompt: The students donated books for the class book corner. There are 252 story books. The literature and art books are story books (5/6), and the science and technology books are literature and art books (2/3). How many science and technology books are donated?
summary: var1 = [find](number of story books) #252, var2 = [find](proportion of literature and art books) #5/6, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 252 * 5/6 = 210, var4 = [find](proportion of science and technology books as literature and art books) #2/3, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 210 * 2/3 = 140, [return](var5) # 140

prompt: Xiaohua's mother brought 50 yuan to buy vegetables, 25.35 yuan to buy meat dishes, and 8.15 yuan to buy vegetarian dishes. How much money do you have left?
summary: var1 = [find](money brought by Xiaohua's mother) #50, var2 = [find](cost of meat dishes) #25.35, var3 = [find](cost of vegetarian dishes) #8.15, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 25.35 + 8.15 = 33.5, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 50 - 33.5 = 16.5, [return](var5) # 16.5

prompt: There were originally 9 rows of seats in the lecture theater, with 20 chairs in each row. During a meeting, 48 chairs were temporarily added. How many chairs are there in this lecture theater?
summary: var1 = [find](number of rows of seats) #9, var2 = [find](number of chairs in each row) #20, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 9 * 20 = 180, var4 = [find](number of temporarily added chairs) #48, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 180 + 48 = 228, [return](var5) # 228

prompt: Dad bought 2 bags of monosodium glutamate, paid 50 yuan, and got back 44 yuan. How much does each bag of MSG sell?
summary: var1 = [find](total amount paid by dad) #50, var2 = [find](amount of change received by dad) #44, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 50 - 44 = 6, var4 = [find](number of bags of MSG) #2, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 6 / 2 = 3, [return](var5) # 3

prompt: The fruit store shipped 480 kilograms of apples. They were loaded into 2 trucks, and each truck contained 40 boxes. How many kilograms were loaded in each box on average?
summary: var1 = [find](total weight of apples) #480, var2 = [find](number of trucks) #2, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 480 / 2 = 240, var4 = [find](number of boxes per truck) #40, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 240 / 40 = 6, [return](var5) # 6

prompt: The road construction team wanted to build a road with a length of 875 meters. They built 220 meters on the first day and 297 meters on the second day. How many meters are left unrepaired?
summary: var1 = [find](length of road to be built) #875, var2 = [find](length of road built on day 1) #220, var3 = [find](length of road built on day 2) #297, var4 = [add](var2, var3) # 220 + 297 = 517, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 875 - 517 = 358, [return](var5) # 358

prompt: The children made 62 big red flowers and gave 27 to the kindergarten. The remaining big red flowers were divided into 5 shares on average. How many flowers are there in each share?
summary: var1 = [find](total number of big red flowers made by children) #62, var2 = [find](number of big red flowers given to kindergarten) #27, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 62 - 27 = 35, var4 = [find](number of shares for remaining flowers) #5, var5 = [divide](var3, var4) # 35 / 5 = 7, [return](var5) # 7

prompt: Zhang Hua rode a bicycle from school to the Children's Palace. It is known that he rode a bicycle at 210 meters per minute. After 8 minutes, he was still 140 meters away from the Children's Palace. How many meters is it from the school to the Children's Palace?
summary: var1 = [find](speed of Zhang Hua on bicycle) #210 meters/minute, var2 = [find](time taken by Zhang Hua) #8 minutes, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 210 * 8 = 1680 meters, var4 = [find](distance left to Children's Palace) #140 meters, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 1680 + 140 = 1820 meters, [return](var5) # 1820

prompt: There are 4 classes in the third grade, with an average of 45 students in each class, and each person buys 2 homework books. How many homework books should be bought in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of classes) #4, var2 = [find](average number of students per class) #45, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4 * 45 = 180, var4 = [find](number of homework books each person buys) #2, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 180 * 2 = 360, [return](var5) # 360

prompt: A piece of parallelogram land has a base of 150m and a height of 60m. A total of 6300kg of wheat is harvested. How many kilograms of wheat are harvested on average per square meter?
summary: var1 = [find](base of parallelogram land) #150, var2 = [find](height of parallelogram land) #60, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 150 * 60 = 9000, var4 = [find](total amount of wheat harvested) #6300, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 6300 / 9000 = 0.7, [return](var5) # 0.7

prompt: The school cafeteria bought 38.25 kilograms of tomatoes and 21.08 kilograms of cucumbers. The celery bought was 4.35 kilograms less than the sum of tomatoes and cucumbers. How many kilograms of celery were bought?
summary: var1 = [find](kilograms of tomatoes) #38.25, var2 = [find](kilograms of cucumbers) #21.08, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 38.25 + 21.08 = 59.33, var4 = [find](kilograms of celery less than sum of tomatoes and cucumbers) #4.35, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 59.33 - 4.35 = 54.98, [return](var5) # 54.98

prompt: The school library has newly purchased 25 sets of the same extra-curricular books, each set has 4 books, and the total cost is 1,000 yuan. How much is each extracurricular book?
summary: var1 = [find](number of sets of books) #25, var2 = [find](number of books in each set) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1,var2) # 25 * 4 = 100, var4 = [find](total cost) #1000, var5 = [divide](var4,var3) # 1000 / 100 = 10, [return](var5) # 10

prompt: There used to be 802 story books in the library, but 387 were lent out at noon, and 295 were returned before school in the afternoon. How many story books are there in the library now?
summary: var1 = [find](initial number of story books) #802, var2 = [find](number of books lent out at noon) #387, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 802 - 387 = 415, var4 = [find](number of books returned before school) #295, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 415 + 295 = 710, [return](var5) # 710

prompt: There are 105 buildings in Haocheng Tianxia, ​​each with 48 suites, and 43 unoccupied ones. How many are occupied?
summary: var1 = [find](number of buildings) #105, var2 = [find](suites per building) #48, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 105 * 48 = 5040, var4 = [find](number of unoccupied suites) #43, var5 = [subtract](var3, var4) # 5040 - 43 = 4997, [return](var5) # 4997

prompt: There are 37 people in Class 5 (3). If each person recycles 1.5 kg of waste paper on average, 1 kg of waste paper can produce 0.8 kg of recycled paper. How many kilograms of recycled paper can be produced from recycled waste paper?
summary: var1 = [find](number of people in Class 5 (3)) #37, var2 = [find](average kg of waste paper recycled per person) #1.5, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 37 * 1.5 = 55.5, var4 = [find](kg of recycled paper produced from 1 kg of waste paper) #0.8, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 55.5 * 0.8 = 44.4, [return](var5) # 44.4

prompt: Two people, A and B, are walking in the same direction from cities A and B, which are 36 kilometers apart. B is in front and A is behind. A travels 15 kilometers per hour, and B travels 6 kilometers per hour. How many hours later can A catch up with B?
summary: var1 = [find](distance between city A and city B) #36, var2 = [find](speed of person A) #15, var3 = [find](speed of person B) #6, var4 = [subtract](var2, var3) # 15 - 6 = 9, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 36 / 9 = 4, [return](var5) # 4

prompt: It is 4.25 yuan per kilogram of oranges. My mother bought 14 kilograms and paid the salesperson 100 yuan. How much should I get back?
summary: var1 = [find](cost per kilogram of oranges) #4.25, var2 = [find](weight of oranges bought by mother) #14, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 4.25 * 14 = 59.5, var4 = [find](amount paid by mother) #100, var5 = [subtract](var4, var3) # 100 - 59.5 = 40.5, [return](var5) # 40.5

prompt: Autumn is the harvest season, and the animals also come to help. It takes (1/12) an hour for a monkey to pick a basket of apples. It picks 26 baskets in the morning and 22 baskets in the afternoon. How many hours did it take the monkey to pick the apples?
summary: var1 = [find](number of baskets picked in the morning) #26, var2 = [find](number of baskets picked in the afternoon) #22, var3 = [add](var1, var2) # 26 + 22 = 48, var4 = [find](time taken to pick one basket) #(1/12) of an hour, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 48 x (1/12) = 4, [return](var5) # 4

prompt: The school organizes a hand-made competition. There are 12 tutors in total. Each group of 8 students is divided into 11 works. There are 1664 students from the whole school participating in the competition. How many works did the students of the whole school make in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of tutors) #12, var2 = [find](number of students participating) #1664, var3 = [divide](var2, 8) # 1664 / 8 = 208, var4 = [find](number of works per group) #11, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 208 * 11 = 2288, [return](var5) # 2288

prompt: Xiaohong goes to the post office and buys 6 sets of stamps at 12 yuan each, and another stamp album at 39 yuan each. How much did Xiaohong spend in total?
summary: var1 = [find](number of sets of stamps) #6, var2 = [find](cost of each set of stamps) #12, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 * 12 = 72, var4 = [find](cost of stamp album) #39, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 72 + 39 = 111, [return](var5) # 111

prompt: There used to be 427 kilograms of rice in the canteen of Xinxing School. After eating 300 kilograms last week, another 325 kilograms of rice was shipped in. How many kilograms of rice are there in the canteen now?
summary: var1 = [find](initial amount of rice) #427, var2 = [find](amount of rice eaten last week) #300, var3 = [subtract](var1, var2) # 427 - 300 = 127, var4 = [find](amount of rice shipped in), #325, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 127 + 325 = 452, [return](var5) # 452

prompt: The school has 6 grades and each grade has 4 classes. There are 1,200 people in the school, which happens to be full. How many students are there on average in each class?
summary: var1 = [find](number of grades) #6, var2 = [find](number of classes per grade) #4, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 6 * 4 = 24, var4 = [find](total number of people in school) #1200, var5 = [divide](var4, var3) # 1200 / 24 = 50, [return](var5) # 50

prompt: Mr. Wang’s family has a parallelogram-shaped vegetable field with a base length of 8 meters and a height of 6 meters. It is known that an average of 15 kilograms of vegetables can be harvested per square meter. How many kilograms of vegetables can be harvested in this vegetable field?
summary: var1 = [find](base length of parallelogram-shaped vegetable field) #8, var2 = [find](height of parallelogram-shaped vegetable field) #6, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 8 * 6 = 48, var4 = [find](average yield of vegetables per square meter) #15, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 48 * 15 = 720, [return](var5) # 720

prompt: It has been 16 days to build a canal, 37 meters per day, and there are still 146 meters that have not been repaired. How long is this canal in meters?
summary: var1 = [find](number of days to build the canal) #16, var2 = [find](distance covered per day) #37, var3 = [multiply](var1, var2) # 16 * 37 = 592, var4 = [find](distance left to be covered) #146, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 592 + 146 = 738, [return](var5) # 738

prompt: A bridge pier is 36 meters high above the water, the underwater part accounts for 15% of the total length, and the part buried in the mud accounts for 1/4 of the total length. How many meters is the total length of the bridge pier?
summary: var1 = [find](height of bridge pier) #36, var2 = [find](percentage of total length that is underwater) #15%, var3 = [find](percentage of total length that is buried in mud) #25%, var4 = [subtract](1, [add](var2, var3)) # 1 - (15% + 25%) = 60%, var5 = [divide](var1, var4) # 36 / 0.6 = 60, [return](var5) # 60

prompt: There are 600 exercise books in the stationery store. After selling some, there are 4 packs left, each pack of 25 books. How many copies are sold?
summary: var1 = [find](initial number of exercise books) #600, var2 = [find](number of books per pack) #25, var3 = [find](total number of packs left) #4, var4 = [multiply](var2, var3) # 25 * 4 = 100, var5 = [subtract](var1, var4) # 600 - 100 = 500, [return](var5) # 500

prompt: The apprentice processed 72 parts in 9 hours, and the master processed 15 more parts per hour than the apprentice on average. How many parts does the master process per hour?
summary: var1 = [find](number of parts processed by apprentice) #72, var2 = [find](number of hours worked by apprentice) #9, var3 = [divide](var1, var2) # 72 / 9 = 8, var4 = [find](additional parts processed by master per hour) #15, var5 = [add](var3, var4) # 8 + 15 = 23, [return](var5) # 23

prompt: The apprentice processes 48 parts per hour. The number of parts he can process in 5 hours can be completed by the master in only 4 hours. How many parts does the master process per hour?

prompt: The Shanghai-Nanjing Adjustment Highway runs from Shanghai to Nanjing via Wuxi, with a total length of 272 kilometers. A car departs from Shanghai at a speed of 105 kilometers per hour and arrives in Wuxi after 1.2 hours. How many kilometers is the expressway from Wuxi to Nanjing?

prompt: There are 156 skipping ropes in the sports group, and 5 groups of children participate in the rope skipping competition. Each group needs 8 skipping ropes. Ask: How many skipping ropes are left?

prompt: The grain store shipped 480 kg of flour, and the rice shipped was 100 kg more than five times the amount of flour. How many kilograms of rice did the grain store ship?

prompt: Car A travels 32 kilometers per hour, and car B travels 34 kilometers per hour. The two cars leave opposite places at the same time and meet each other after 3 hours. How many kilometers are the distance between the two places?

prompt: A train of freight trains and a train of passenger trains depart from places A and B at the same time. summary: var1 = [find](speed of passenger train) #60, var2 = [find](speed of freight train) #(4/5) * var1 # (4/5) * 60 = 48, var3 = [find](time until meeting) #4, var4 = [add](var1, var2) # 60 + 48 = 108, var5 = [multiply](var3, var4) # 4 * 108 = 432, [return](var5) # 432

prompt: A garment factory processes a batch of work clothes. It takes 2.1 meters of cloth to make a jacket, 1.2 meters of cloth to make a pair of trousers, and purchases 85.8 meters of cloth. How many sets of work clothes can be processed?

prompt: There are 16 sticks of red chalk on Teacher Zhao's desk. The number of sticks of white chalk is that of red chalk (5/4), and that of blue chalk (10/11). How many sticks of blue chalk are there?

prompt: Xiaohong and Xiaoming are running on the circular track. They start from the same place at the same time and walk in opposite directions. Xiao Hong runs 220 meters per minute, Xiao Ming runs 180 meters per minute, and they meet after 2 minutes. How many meters is the runway long?

prompt: Master Wang plans to make 1,500 parts. He has done it for 5 days and completed 5% every day. How many parts are left?
